data.title: TotalEnergies secures 2 million tons/year Alaska LNG deal for 20 years, targeting Asia market, making strategic move.
data.description: TotalEnergies SE (NYSE: TTE) recently finalized a preliminary agreement with Glenfarne to secure a significant long-term supply of liquefied natural gas (LNG) from the Alaska LNG project, marking a strategic move for the company. The deal involves acquiring 2 million tons of LNG annually for a period of 20 years, pending the final investment decision of the project. Despite this development, TTE shares are currently underperforming in the market. The Alaska LNG project holds a strategic location on the U.S. Pacific coast, serving as the sole federally authorized LNG export terminal in the area. It is planned to have a capacity of 20 million tons per year, with a primary focus on catering to the Asian LNG market, the largest globally, thereby enhancing energy security and transpacific connections. This agreement underscores TotalEnergies' goal to bolster its position as a prominent U.S. LNG buyer while diversifying its sources of supply. As of 2025, the company emerged as the top U.S. LNG exporter, shipping 19 million tons. For the full article, refer to Benzinga.com.

data.title: Elisa and Elisa Industriq to showcase innovations at MWC Barcelona 2026. Event on March 2-5. Finnish telecom leader.
data.description: Elisa, a prominent telecommunications and digital services company based in Finland, along with its international software division Elisa Industriq, is set to showcase a strong presence at the upcoming Mobile World Congress (MWC) in Barcelona from March 2 to March 5, 2026. This event is significant for Elisa as it presents an opportunity for them to highlight their innovations and advancements in the industry to a global audience. The MWC is expected to attract thousands of participants and industry professionals, providing Elisa with a valuable platform to network and demonstrate their cutting-edge technologies.
